==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dunnage
<hw>Dun"nage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Dun</er> a
mound.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Fagots, boughs, or loose materials
of any kind, laid on the bottom of the hold for the cargo to rest upon
to prevent injury by water, or stowed among casks and other cargo to
prevent their motion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dunner</ent>⟦br⟧
